-- Rwanda plans to privatise development bank - ministry
-- 
-- Sat Apr 05, 2014 05:44AM EDT
-- None



KIGALI, April 5 (Reuters) - Rwanda's government plans to privatise the Development Bank of Rwanda in a bid to reform its operation, the Finance Ministry said in a brief statement.

More details of the privatisation would be released on Sunday at a news briefing, it added. "The Government of Rwanda plans to privatisee the Development Bank of Rwanda (BRD) in a move to reform its operation and ensure that the bank effectively serves its mandate," the ministry statement said.